title: Suspect in murder of family of 4 near Chicago found dead in Oklahoma
description: A man sought in connection to the slaying of a family of four in the Chicago suburb of Romeoville was found dead inside a burning car in Oklahoma, authorities said Wednesday.

title: Maps: How rainfall turned into floods in Libya
description: Heavy rainfall in Libya devastated Derna, where major flooding occurred after poorly maintained dams burst. Learn more about the severity of the Derna floods.

title: Missing F-35 jet was flying 'inverted' before crash, eyewitnesses say
description: WILLIAMSBURG COUNTY, S.C. — A South Carolina couple had been celebrating their son's 7th birthday on Sunday afternoon when they looked to the skies.

title: U.S. senators ask Biden admin to push for release of Princeton grad student held by Iran-backed militia
description: Senators Menendez and Booker want the Biden administration to ask Iraq to win release of Elizabeth Tsurkov, a Princeton student held by an Iran-backed militia.

title: Law enforcement staff raised concerns about Ron DeSantis' top crime talking point
description: A top crime statistic used by Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis is based on incomplete data — and was flagged as problematic by law enforcement staffers.

title: Federal Reserve pauses interest rate hikes as inflation and economy slow down
description: The Federal Reserve left the main U.S. interest rate unchanged Wednesday as it waits to see if its historic series of rate hikes over the last 18 months will get inflation under control.

title: White House told U.S. ambassador to Japan to stop taunting China on social media
description: President Joe Biden’s aides have asked that Rahm Emanuel, the U.S. ambassador to Japan, stop posting messages on social media taunting Chinese President Xi Jinping, according to three administration officials.

title: Sen. John Fetterman says he'll 'save democracy' by wearing a suit if House GOP avoids shutdown
description: Sen. John Fetterman, D-Penn., on Wednesday offered to "save democracy by wearing a suit on the Senate floor next week" if House Republicans "stop trying to shut our government down."

title: Ultraprocessed foods linked to depression, study finds
description: Consuming large amounts of ultraprocessed foods may be linked to depression, research published Wednesday found. Ultraprocessed foods are high in salt, sugar, hydrogenated fats and additives.

title: Wildfires are destroying decades of clean air efforts
description: Increases in wildfire smoke are reversing decades of improvements to air quality in some parts of the U.S., according to new research.

title: Alabama band director says he was 'stunned and baffled' after getting tased at football game
description: An Alabama band director who was shocked with a stun gun by police after he refused to stop his band's performance said he is "stunned and baffled" by what happened.

title: Patriots fan who died after stadium fight didn't suffer traumatic injury, had 'medical issue'
description: A New England Patriots fan didn't suffer from "traumatic" injuries when he collapsed at a game and later died, officials said Wednesday, suggesting his death may not be linked to a fight at the stadium.

title: Donald Trump Jr.’s X account apparently hacked, announces father's death
description: In a tweet that now appears to be deleted, Donald Trump Jr.’s X account appeared to post that his father had died. A spokesperson said his account was hacked.

title: Merrick Garland faces grilling from House Republicans on Trump and Hunter Biden cases
description: Linkout

title: On Hurricane Maria anniversary, Puerto Rican groups push Congress on tax breaks, food security
description: On the sixth anniversary of Hurricane Maria, several Puerto Rican groups seek congressional action around food security and assistance and an end to tax breaks they say benefit the wealthy at islanders' expense.

title: Elon Musk’s X, formerly Twitter, ranks last in climate misinformation ‘scorecard’
description: Environmental groups slammed Elon Musk’s X app, formerly known as Twitter, in a report ranking social media platforms on their approach to climate misinformation.

title: FDA rejects first needle-free alternative to EpiPens, calling for additional research
description: The nasal-spray Neffy was rejected by the FDA. The epinephrine nasal spray would've been the first needle-free alternative to EpiPens, but the FDA said additional research was needed.

title: Patriots fan was punched in head before he died at stadium, witness says
description: A New England Patriots fan who died at a home game Sunday was punched in the head twice before the medical emergency, a witness said Tuesday.

title: Questions mount after U.S. fighter jet went missing
description: Military investigators are facing questions about why an F-35 stealth fighter jet went missing for more than 24 hours.

title: Paramount+ removes Russell Brand comedy special amid sex assault claims
description: Paramount+ has removed one of Russell Brand's stand-up comedy specials after several women accused him of sexual assault, according to a source with knowledge of the situation.
